    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-7">
        <h2></h2>
        
            <div class="gen-group">
              
                <div class="gen-group__logo"><img src="https://d1o1wdbk5ytaqh.cloudfront.net/media/Screen_Shot_2015-09-23_at_11.26.59.png" /></div>
              
              <div class="gen-group__content">
                <p class="subheading">Site managed by</p>
                <h2>The Olde House Solar</h2>
              </div>
            </div>
        
        <div class="gen-content">
          <p>The Olde House is a family-owned holiday cottage business on Penpont Farm. The Hawkey Family first bought the farm 100 years ago, and in 1976 started converting their old stone barns into self-catering cottages. Since the 1970s, the family-run business has grown to hold 30 cottages, a swimming pool and kids play areas all situated on the farm. </p>
<p>Brothers Shaun and Oliver Hawkey now run two businesses on the farm. Shaun runs The Olde House, the farmstay holiday business with 242kW solar, while Oliver runs the 550 acre working farm, which has the 100kW <a href="http://piclo.uk/p/penpont-farm-solar/z8xUl#">Penpont Farm Solar</a> installation. </p>
<p>The Olde House solar installation is part of a wider green approach for the business, as the family looks to create a sustainable business while reducing its carbon footprint. All visitors and guests can charge their electric cars for free through two electric car charge points on site. The family has also recently installed a 199 kW wood chip-fuelled biomass boiler to heat a selection of cottages and the swimming pool.</p>
<p>Revenue generated by export electricity is used to pay back the loan used to finance the installation. This is nearly paid off - and once it is, the revenue will be re-invested in the business, allowing the Hawkey family to maintain the property and build new cottages.</p>
          <p class="read-more"><a href="#" class="button">Read More</a></p>
        </div>
        

